Home Sales Revenue

Revenues from home sales increased 17% to $3.7 billion (12,497 homes closed) for
the three months ended June 30, 2017 from $3.1 billion (10,739 homes closed) in
the prior year period. Revenues from home sales increased 18% to $9.6 billion
(32,586 homes closed) for the nine months ended June 30, 2017 from $8.1 billion
(28,062 homes closed) in the prior year period. The overall increase in home
sales revenues reflects the continued stable to moderately improved market
conditions in most of our markets.

The number of homes closed increased 16% in both the three and nine months ended
June 30, 2017 compared to the prior year periods due to increases in all of our
regions. Our Phoenix, Florida and South Carolina markets contributed the most to
higher closings volumes in our Southwest, Southeast and East regions,
respectively. The average selling price of homes closed during the three and
nine months ended June 30, 2017 was $293,100 and $295,200, respectively, up
slightly from the prior year periods.


